TY  - JOUR
AU  - Leippold, Markus
AU  - Wu, Liuren
T1  - Design and Estimation of Multi-Currency Quadratic Models*
PY  - 2007
Y1  - 2007/01/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfl002
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 11
IS  - 2
SP  - 167
EP  - 207
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - To simultaneously account for the properties of interest-rate term structure and foreign exchange rates within one arbitrage-free framework, we propose a class of multi-currency quadratic models (MCQM) with an (m + n) factor structure in the pricing kernel of each economy. The m factors model the term structure of interest rates. The n factors capture the portion of the exchange rate movement that is independent of the term structure. Our modeling framework represents the first in the literature that not only explicitly allows independent currency movement, but also guarantees internal consistency across all economies without imposing any artificial constraints on the exchange rate dynamics. We estimate a series of multi-currency quadratic models using U.S. and Japanese LIBOR and swap rates and the exchange rate between the two economies. Estimation shows that independent currency factors are essential in releasing the tension between the currency movement and the term structure of interest rates.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfl002
ER  - 



